    "□ Proposition 7.2.",
    "The representation π X C = π 1 • ρ X C is irreducible, and there is a unitary equivalence, π X C ≃ π X e.The strategy for showing that π X C is irreducible is to show that all of its vector states are pure.",
    "In fact, it is sufficient to show this for vector states corresponding to a dense subset of the unit ball of H.Let us consider a unit vector in H of the form |Ψ⟩ = π 1 (O)|Ω⟩ for some O ∈ A loc.",
    "This defines a vector state ψ in π X C byψ(x):= ⟨Ψ, π X C (x)Ψ⟩ = ⟨Ω, π 1 O * ρ X (x)O Ω⟩for all x ∈ A.",
    "Our goal is to show that ψ is also a vector state of the GNS representation π X e. First note that the state ψ can be obtained as the limit of a sequence of vector states of the vacuum representation π 1 as follows."
